There are two ways to convert cascading `tvm_if_then_else`s. For example,

```
a = tvm_if_then_else(..., w, x) + tvm_if_then_else(..., y, z)
```

can be converted to be

(1)
```c
if (...) {
    if (...) {
        a = w + y;
    } else {
        a = w + z;
    }
} else {
    if (...) {
        a = x + y;
    } else {
        a = x + z;
    }
}
```

or

(2)
```c
int tmp1
if (...) {
    tmp1 = w;
} else {
    tmp1 = x;
}
int tmp2
if (...) {
    tmp2 = y;
} else {
    tmp2 = z;
}
a = tmp1 + tmp2;
```

The current implementation is (1). Maybe I can change to (2), but I don't know if there are any overhead of storing into and then loading from intermediate variables.

